NAVE v. KRIETE et al. (Supreme Court, Appellate Term. April 10, 1908.) Courts—Municipal Coubts—Appeal—Defective Recobd. Where, on appeal to the Appellate Term from a Municipal Court judgment, the return was defective for failure to contain the complaint and answer, the record would be returned to the files of the court for correction. Appeal from Municipal Court, Borough of Manhattan, Twelfth District. Action by Mark D. Nave against Otto Kriete and another. From a Municipal Court judgment for plaintiff, defendants appeal. Record returned to files for correction.

Argued before GILDERSLEEVE, P. J., and SEABURY and DAYTON, JJ.

*720Holm, Whitlock & Scarff, for appellants. Henry Brill, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

The return herein is defective, in that there is no complaint or answer therein.

Record returned to files of the court to await such action as counsel may deem proper.
